Syndicate Hub reopened at 5225 Brady Street in October 1993 then moved to it's current location of 2211 East 52nd in Davenport in January 2000 where it is locally owned and operated by Mere and Sue Brunsma.  Syndicate Hub is proud to be associated with some of the world's finest high-quality, brand name men's clothing designers.

Description: Solar Desalination - Sun Trio™ and Solar Cogeneration - SunDuo™
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Beltane Solar is at the nexus of energy, water and agriculture. The Company has three products scheduled for production: •The SunDuo™ T16 is a roof or ground mounted solar/thermal system with low cost combined heat and power. •The SunDuo™ G16 is a ground-mounted solar/thermal system for uneven terrain ideal for off-grid applications. •The SunTrio™ combines either the T16 or the G16 with a desalination system built to Beltane’s specification and private label manufactured for distribution. SunDuo™ creates electricity and hot water from a solar photovoltaic and thermal receiver. Reflectors concentrate sunlight, reducing the PV cells required by 93%. The receiver captures the valuable thermal energy produced by cooling PV cells so they operate more efficiently. The thermal energy is used by C&I CHP customers to offset the cost of their water heating requirements. Integrated tracking collects 30-40% more energy throughout the day and collects 60-100% more energy during peak utility demand charge periods in the late afternoon. We have determined that the scalable SunDuo™ has the lowest levelized cost of electricity in its market and the highest IRR in its class. SunTrio™ systems are designed for the distributed desalination market for the production of agricultural, industrial and drinking water. It provides a scalable distributed solution combining SunDuo™ collectors with proven, private labeled desalination systems. The point-of-use system is deployable in underserved areas that have extensive brackish water resources. Unlike brick-and-mortar facilities, the SunTrio™ does not require infrastructure and pipelines. The cost of water produced by a fossil fuel dependent desalination plant will increase with inflation but a solar powered system fixes energy costs over a 20 plus year period in locations without affordable energy or a grid. The SunTrio™ is designed to be installed in a short period of time with minimal or no permitting and can be redeployed elsewhere.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Consumer Electronics, Energy, Hardware, Manufacturing, Natural Resources, Sustainability

Description: Offbeat Guides develops customized travel guides with up-to-date information for individuals.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: [Offbeat Guides](http://www.offbeatguides.com/) makes customized travel guides with up-to-date information related to your trip.  After a user enters answers to 5 questions (name, home town, destination, travel dates and where they are staying), Offbeat guides creates a personalized guide for the user's trip using data from both open (wikipedia, wikitravel, Flickr and Google Maps) and proprietary sources.  Guides can be purchased in two formats - full color printed guides are available for $24.95 or downloadable guides in PDF format can be had for $9.95.  Guides include maps, events in the city you are visiting when you're there, the most current exchange rates, key phrases in the city's language, a weather forecast based on your travel dates and much more. Offbeat Guides was founded by [Dave Sifry](http://www.crunchbase.com/person/dave-sifry), who previously founded [Technorati](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/technorati).

Description: LegalSherpa enables entrepreneurs to carry out filing trademark and copyright applications.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: LegalSherpa was created to provide entrepreneurs the most cost effective option for filing trademark and copyright applications. Trademark Registration:  Obtaining a federal trademark registration amplifies the protection your mark receives, discourages others from using your mark, and provides greater legal remedies.  LegalSherpa provides an easy to use online trademark application questionnaire and electronically files the owners federal trademark application with the U.S. Patent & Trademark Office. Copyright Registration:  When people speak of copyrighting their work, they usually mean registering it with the U.S. Copyright Office. Copyright registration occurs when a copyright owner makes public, basic information about their copyrighted work in the U.S. Copyright Office. This basic information includes information such as who owns the copyright, the title of the work, and when and who wrote the work. To register with the U.S. Copyright Office, you must complete the appropriate application, pay an application fee, and submit copies of the copyrighted work to the Copyright Office.  LegalSherpa provides an easy to use online copyright application questionnaire and electronically files the owners federal copyright application with the U.S. Copyright Office.
